-- Abkhazia Vice President Wounded in Grenade Attack on Home, Interfax Says
-- B y   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a
-- 2010-09-23T04:31:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/abkhazia-vice-president-wounded-in-grenade-attack-on-home-interfax-says.html
The vice president of the breakaway
Georgian region of Abkhazia was wounded in a grenade attack at
his home, Interfax reported, citing Alexander Ankvab, the
victim.  Ankvab told the Moscow-based news service that he suffered
injuries to the leg and arm. Abkhaz President Sergei Bagapsh
said the assault was an attempt to destabilize the country,
which is recognized as independent by Russia, Interfax reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Kolesnikova in Moscow at 
